Example
Return the hostname and port of the current URL:

Copy
let x = location.host;

Description
The host property gets and sets the host name and port of a URL.

If the port number is not specified in the URL or if it is the scheme's default port - like 80, some browsers will not display the port number.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
host	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Return the host property:

Copy
let a = location.host;
Set the host property:

Copy
location.host = hostname:port;
Property Values
Value	Type	Description
hostname:port	String	the hostname and port number of the URL
Return Value
A String, representing the domain name and port number, or the IP address of a URL.

